The paper focuses on computer vision tasks and proposes a method for interpreting the internal representations learned by deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses learning-based representations, which suggests a connection to machine learning, specifically deep learning. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the evaluation of the proposed method, which involves quantitative analysis, indicating a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of heatmap visualizations, which suggests a connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and natural language processing.
